@*<div id="splash"></div>*@

<div id="content">
    <div class="post">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: xx-large; color: #FF9900; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            MCA Entrance Test
        </h2>
        <div class="entry">            
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">                
                Candidate should clear one of the below Entrance Test:<br /><br />
                ➢ PGCET (Post Graduate Common Entrance Test) - conducted by Karnataka government
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 14px;">
                ➢ KMAT (Karnataka Management Aptitude Test) - conducted by Private College Management Association
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="post">
        <h2 style="font-size: xx-large; color: #FF9900; font-weight: lighter; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            Procedure
        </h2>
        <div class="entry" style="font-size: 18px;">
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 1: Check for Eligibility -
                </span>
                First check to see if you are eligible for the course. Go to the web page that enlists the requirements for your chosen course. If you satisfy these conditions, feel free to apply.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 2: Collect your form -
                </span>
                Application Forms can now be downloaded from the college website as well as collected from the office. The application form are issued are as follows:On the day of the Bangalore University III Year results.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 3: Take the Entrance Test -
                </span>
                Find out the date fixed for the objective type examination. Ensure that you take the examination for it will not be repeated.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 4: Submit your form -
                </span>
                Ensure that your form is filled as per instructions. Enclose a photocopy of the statement of marks for the last examination passed. Do not enclose originals. While submitting the application form at the college office pay a fee of Rs.200.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 5: Check the Interview status -
                </span>
                The college notice board displays the selected numbers and the date and time of the interview. Make sure you check it regularly. If you miss the date, you could  lose your seat.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 6: Attend the Interview -
                </span>
                Bring your parents and carry the following with you Two Stamp size photographs Original Marks card and two photocopies of the same Original Transfer  Certificate Certificate of Good Conduct Migration Certificate( if you are not a  Karnataka SSLC\PUC\DEGREE student) Original and three copies of Caste Certificate (for SC, ST and BT students only)
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 7: Pay the fees -
                </span>
                This  has to be done on the day of the interview. The fees are printed on the application form or notified on the College notice board.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px;">
                <span style="font-weight: bold">
                    ➢ Stage 8 : Congratulations and Welcome to the Mount Carmel Family -
                </span>
                Wait for the opening day and the Orientation Programme. The Orientation  Programme is designed to give you a taste of life at Mount Carmel College-your second home for the next few years.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="clear: both;">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
